description:
&lt;p&gt;We have an exciting opportunity for a suitably qualified Occupational Therapist to join The Community Therapy Team In Furness. This exciting new OT post is a first for the team and is to support an MDT approach in the delivery of the post-covid rehabilitation pathways&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This service provides adult general community therapy and rehabilitation In the Furness Locality. Patients are seen in their own homes and also in nursing and residential care care settings.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Community therapy services are currently aligning to the Integrated Care Community structure, supporting the health needs of the local population, registered to a GP practice, thus enhancing multi-disciplinary team working.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The community therapy team supports clients to progress through their rehabilitation journey and support the transfer of care into the community setting, when clients have ongoing therapy needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post will offer the successful candidate the opportunity to work within a proactive multidisciplinary team with partners from health and social care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Full and part time or secondment applications will be considered.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Anyone newly appointed to the trust will be subject to the completion of a satisfactory 6 month probationary period (this includes bank staff). This will give the new staff member an opportunity to become familiar with the role and working environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
